    <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
      <p>In 1978-1978, Lembi Kongas, a trained anthropologist, conducted an oral history project with farm women who lived in Southern Michigan. The interviews were later published in two volumes entitled <title render="italic">Farm women in the Twentieth Century: A view from southern Michigan.</title> </p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
      <p>The Kongas collection consists of the results of the project to document the lives of farm women living in Southern Michigan. The collection includes tapes of oral interviews, transcripts of the interviews, background materials, and miscellaneous photographs and slides.</p>
    </scopecontent>
